% rebase('layout.tpl', title='Home Page', year=year)

<div class="jumbotron">
    <h1>JogRX</h1>
	<h2>{{ title }}.</h2>
	<form  action="/permissions" method="post" class="form-horizontal" role="form">
    <div class="form-group">
      <div class="col-sm-10">
        <p>The decorator API is quite limited, though. You don’t know anything about the route being decorated or the associated application object and have no way to efficiently store data that is shared among all routes. But fear not! Plugins are not limited to just decorator functions. Bottle accepts anything as a plugin as long as it is callable or implements an extended API. This API is described below and gives you a lot of control over the whole process.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="form-group">        
      <div class="col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-10">
        <input value="Accept"  type="submit" name="Accept" class="btn btn-default active"/> <input value="Decline"  type="submit" name="Decline" class="btn btn-default active" />
      </div>
    </div>   

  </form>
</div>

